t21.text: Creating a FB account requires an ID check. When that ID check is done the IP is recorded. The metrics sitting behind the algorithms are complex but you won’t bypass them with your fake account so be very careful what you write bcos you can be tracked.

t22.text: I have NEVER created a FAKE account. My name is OPENLY on TWO FB accounts (my own name & my dogs account). If u accuse me of having any other FAKE accounts I will SUE you. My credibility is important to me. My reputation is at stake. I will not be the target for false claims.

t23.text: Creating fake accounts to snoop on people is more common than you think. There are a huge number of fake accounts for all manner of purposes. Jeez even my dog has an account. But when the fake tips over in to criminal activity, now that’s w whole new ball game.

t24.text: If a FB profile is being used for intimidation, dangerous or illegal content, or to incite hate or crime, it CAN be traced. FB holds records which are accessible by law enforcement. Your identity WILL be found out
